  "texts": [
    "However, the unigram model does not account for the order and context of words.",
    "During feature extraction, the tweet's content is processed to produce a feature vector for each tweet, where each element represents the occurrence or frequency of a specific word from the vocabulary.",
    "Models based on unigrams are simple and computationally efficient, but they have limitations as they may not capture the semantic information of the text.",
    "To overcome this limitation, the devised model has been extended using bi-grams.",
    "A set of supervised learning algorithms is introduced, providing a brief explanation of how each classifier can be applied in this context:"
